ansforms**\\n\\nI need to avoid using collection transforms that have already been tested since they might be too similar. I wonder if `UIntRange` would be a suitable alternative? Or maybe I could use `ArrayDeque`? However, I need to remember that `ArrayDeque` was added in 1.4 and is public in common, so it's good to keep that in mind while deciding. This is definitely worth exploring further!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering targeted testing**\\n\\nI think we can run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-common:1.6.20`. It might be a bit pricey, but it’s possibly manageable. Since I’m only modifying the test file, I could run a targeted test instead. That could be more efficient, and I wonder if the `test` task includes native as well. I'll keep this in mind as we proceed!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_MBcL0J2xgPNpJD91TC09JF8F|fc_07a7faec10a127fd0169efa32d48cc819e8020b9ca0f3210d1", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2517-4b24971e/tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-common/1.6.20/src/test/kotlin/org_jetbrains_kotlin/kotlin_stdlib_common/Kotlin_stdlib_commonTest.kt", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    fun durationArithmeticAndStringBuildersSummarizeTheTestMatrix() {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    fun arrayDequeSupportsBidirectionalConsumptionWithoutBreakingLogicalOrder() {\n        val releaseStages = ArrayDeque(listOf(\"alpha\", \"beta\"))\n\n        releaseStages.addFirst(\"preview\")\n        releaseStages.addLast(\"stable\")\n\n        val promotedStages = listOf(\n            releaseStages.removeFirst(),\n            releaseStages.removeFirst(),\n        )\n        releaseStages.addFirst(\"candidate\")\n        val rollbackOrder = listOf(\n            releaseStages.removeLast(),\n            releaseStages.removeLast(),\n            releaseStages.removeLast(),\n        )\n\n        assertThat(promotedStages).containsExact